---
// By klok for the Glory of Jesus · 05-2026
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Notice | Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez"
  description="Privacy Notice of Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez S.C. - Personal Data Protection"
  lang="en"
>
  <Navbar />
  <main
    class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-b from-gray-900 via-gray-800 to-gray-900"
  >
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-24">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="mb-8">
          <a
            href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}en`}
            class="inline-flex items-center text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors mb-6"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"></path>
            </svg>
            Back to Home
          </a>
          <h1
            class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-400 to-cyan-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent"
          >
            PRIVACY NOTICE
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-400">
            Federal Law on Protection of Personal Data Held by Private Parties
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-gray-800/50 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-2xl border border-gray-700"
        >
          <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
            <div class="text-gray-300 space-y-6 leading-relaxed">
              <section>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  <strong>BUFETE JURÍDICO PAZOS CHÁVEZ S.C.</strong>,
                  hereinafter (Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez), a legal entity
                  constituted under Mexican law, with address for receiving
                  notifications at Av. Insurgentes Sur # 3155, 2nd Floor, Col.
                  Jardines del Pedregal Cuicuilco, Coyoacán Borough, C.P.
                  04510, Mexico City, is aware of the importance of the
                  legitimate, controlled and informed processing of your
                  personal data. Therefore, Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez makes
                  available to you this Privacy Notice so that you may know its
                  practices when obtaining, using, disclosing or storing your
                  personal data, in accordance with the Federal Law on
                  Protection of Personal Data Held by Private Parties.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  PURPOSE OF DATA PROCESSING
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  The personal data we collect from you will be used for the
                  following purposes, which are necessary for the services you
                  request or which will be provided to you:
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">
                  Primary purposes:
                </h3>

                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-2">
                  Recruitment, selection and hiring of personnel
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">
                  To carry out the process of recruitment, selection and hiring
                  of personnel.
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">
                  Likewise, the information will form part of the company's job
                  pool, and may be transferred for the evaluation and hiring of
                  a third party, or for the evaluation of third parties to whom
                  Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez provides services. It will also
                  be shared with Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez personnel
                  involved in the hiring process, for the purpose of analyzing
                  the results of their functions and producing statistics.
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">
                  The information may be transferred to a third party,
                  outsourcing provider or Financial Institution to process
                  payment for the services rendered to Bufete Jurídico Pazos
                  Chávez.
                </p>
                <ul
                  class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4 mb-4"
                >
                  <li>
                    To generate professional profiles and labor structures,
                    produce statistical reports and evaluate performance.
                  </li>
                  <li>To request personal and labor references of the applicant.</li>
                  <li>
                    Where applicable, to compile the collaborator's file,
                    administer the consideration for services and comply with
                    contractual obligations.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    To maintain communication with the applicant during the
                    recruitment process.
                  </li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-2">
                  Evaluation and selection of suppliers (individuals)
                </h4>

                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-2">
                  Registration and video recording of visitors to the facilities
                  for security reasons
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">
                  It will be processed for statistical, security and
                  surveillance purposes during the time you remain in the
                  building, where applicable, to detect any unlawful activity,
                  or to prove in disputes or judicial and/or administrative
                  requirements the presence or absence of said persons.
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">
                  In case of refusal to be registered and video-recorded, for
                  security reasons you will be denied access to the facilities
                  and, consequently, the continuation of the process.
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  This procedure is indispensable due to internal security
                  policies. The access and candidate registration logs will be
                  kept for 3 months, for the aforementioned purposes.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">
                  Secondary purposes:
                </h3>
                <p class="text-gray-300">No secondary purposes are determined.</p>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  WHAT PERSONAL DATA DO WE COLLECT AND USE FROM YOU?
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  The categories of personal data to be collected and subject
                  to processing are:
                </p>
                <ul
                  class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4 mb-4"
                >
                  <li>
                    <strong>Identification data:</strong> full name, age, date
                    of birth, gender, marital status, address, nationality,
                    email address, home, landline and mobile phone numbers,
                    Federal Taxpayer Registry (RFC), Unique Population Registry
                    Code (CURP), immigration document (where applicable),
                    Social Security Number, photograph, image, signature.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Academic data:</strong> education, languages,
                    aptitudes and skills.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Labor data:</strong> employment history and labor
                    references.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Economic data:</strong> Those derived from
                    socio-economic studies.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Third-party data:</strong> labor history, personal
                    and labor references.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Tax data:</strong> in the case of provision of
                    services as a supplier to Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez, a
                    copy of your Tax Registration.
                  </li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">
                  SENSITIVE DATA:
                </h3>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  <strong>Health data:</strong> collected through the
                  psychometric studies carried out on the candidate.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">
                  CONSENT:
                </h3>
                <p class="text-gray-300">
                  In accordance with the above, the data subject grants their
                  consent in writing for their personal data to be processed in
                  accordance with the terms of this privacy notice.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  MEANS BY WHICH BUFETE JURÍDICO PAZOS CHÁVEZ OBTAINS YOUR DATA
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  We inform you that Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez will obtain
                  your personal data through the following means:
                </p>
                <ol
                  class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4"
                >
                  <li>
                    <strong>In person:</strong> when you are a collaborator or
                    apply for employment, by filling out the job application
                    form that Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez provides.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Direct:</strong> when you provide us with your data
                    to apply for employment through the electronic portals on
                    which Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez publishes its job
                    offers, or when you send us your curriculum vitae as a
                    candidate for a vacancy, via email to any of the addresses
                    of our Human Resources department.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Indirect:</strong> from any other available source
                    of information or one that is permitted by Law.
                  </li>
                </ol>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  USE OF COOKIES AND WEB BEACONS
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300">
                  We inform you that at Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez we do not
                  collect personal data through the use of Cookies or Web
                  Beacons, or other technologies to obtain personal information
                  from you.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  SECURITY MEASURES IMPLEMENTED
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300">
                  For the protection of your personal data we have implemented
                  administrative, physical and technical security measures with
                  the purpose of preventing loss, misuse or alteration of your
                  information.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  TRANSFER OF PERSONAL DATA
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  We inform you that your personal data may be transferred to
                  Mexican and/or foreign third parties and for the following
                  purposes:
                </p>
                <ol
                  class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4 mb-4"
                >
                  <li>
                    Competent authorities for the fulfillment of legal
                    obligations arising from the contractual relationship
                    between the data subject and the controller.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Third parties, clients of Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez, to
                    comply with the contractual obligations acquired by Bufete
                    Jurídico Pazos Chávez for the provision of the service.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Third parties requesting labor references for employees
                    and former employees of Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Third parties arising from corporate restructuring,
                    including merger, consolidation, sale, liquidation or
                    transfer of assets.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Other transmissions provided for in the aforementioned Law
                    and its Regulations.
                  </li>
                </ol>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  The third parties and entities receiving personal data assume
                  the same obligations and/or responsibilities as Bufete
                  Jurídico Pazos Chávez, in accordance with the provisions of
                  this Privacy Notice.
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez undertakes not to transfer your
                  personal information to third parties without your consent,
                  except for the exceptions provided in article 37 of the
                  Federal Law on Protection of Personal Data Held by Private
                  Parties, and to carry out such transfer in the terms set
                  forth in said law.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">
                  OPPOSITION TO THE TRANSFER OF YOUR PERSONAL DATA
                </h3>
                <p class="text-gray-300">
                  Should you wish to oppose the transfer of your personal data,
                  you will have 5 calendar days from the moment you become
                  aware of this privacy notice to express your opposition by
                  written document addressed to the officer indicated in this
                  instrument for the exercise of the ARCO Right, established
                  in this privacy notice. Otherwise, it will be understood that
                  you grant your consent to transfer your data.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  ARCO RIGHTS
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  You or your legal representative have the right to know what
                  personal data we have about you, what we use it for and the
                  conditions of the use we give it (Access). Likewise, it is
                  your right to request the correction of your personal
                  information in case it is outdated, inaccurate or incomplete
                  (Rectification); that we delete it from our records or
                  databases when you consider that it is not being used in
                  accordance with the principles, duties and obligations
                  provided for in the Law (Cancellation); as well as to oppose
                  the use of your personal data for specific purposes
                  (Opposition). These rights are known as ARCO rights and are
                  described in article 29 of the Federal Law on Protection of
                  Personal Data Held by Private Parties.
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  The procedure and requirements for exercising the ARCO rights
                  are as follows:
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  Complete the ARCO right request form FOR GDP 007 (available
                  on the website of Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez:
                  www.pazoschavez.mx) in original and copy bearing the
                  applicant's signature, and deliver it personally at Av.
                  Insurgentes Sur # 3155, 2nd Floor, Col. Jardines del Pedregal
                  Cuicuilco, Coyoacán Borough, C.P. 04510, Mexico City, or by
                  email to <a
                    href="mailto:privacidad@asecon2006.com.mx"
                    class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300"
                    >privacidad@asecon2006.com.mx</a
                  >, attaching the following documentation:
                </p>
                <ol
                  class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4 mb-4"
                >
                  <li>
                    Official identification proving your identity (Voter card
                    issued by the INE, valid Passport, Professional License,
                    or, if you are of foreign nationality, your valid
                    immigration document).
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    If the application is not submitted by the data subject,
                    the document evidencing the representation, together with
                    the identification of the data subject and the legal
                    representative.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    A clear and precise description of the personal data with
                    respect to which you wish to exercise your ARCO Rights.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Any document or information that facilitates the location
                    of your personal data held by Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    In the event of requesting the rectification of data,
                    indicate the modifications to be made and provide the
                    documentation supporting your petition.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Indicate the means and manner in which we may contact you
                    to notify you of the response to your request.
                  </li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">
                  OFFICER IN CHARGE OF HANDLING THE REQUEST
                </h3>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  The Legal Department of Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez is
                  responsible for processing requests from data subjects to
                  exercise the rights contained in the Federal Law on
                  Protection of Personal Data Held by Private Parties.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">
                  TIMEFRAME FOR HANDLING REQUESTS
                </h3>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  The Legal Department of Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez will
                  respond to your request within 20 (twenty) days from the date
                  on which the acknowledgment of receipt is sent. If the
                  request is admissible, the timeframe to carry out the request
                  will be 15 (fifteen) days from the affirmative response.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">
                  REFUSAL TO EXERCISE ARCO RIGHTS
                </h3>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">
                  Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez may refuse the exercise of ARCO
                  Rights in the following cases:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
                  <li>
                    When you are not the data subject or have not proven the
                    representation of the data subject.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    When your personal data does not exist in the company's
                    database.
                  </li>
                  <li>When third-party rights would be infringed.</li>
                  <li>
                    When there is a legal impediment or the decision of a
                    competent authority that restricts your ARCO Rights.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    When the cancellation or opposition has previously been
                    carried out.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  REVOCATION OF CONSENT
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300">
                  You may revoke any consent you may have granted to Bufete
                  Jurídico Pazos Chávez for the processing of your personal
                  data by means of a written document delivered personally to
                  the Officer, provided that such data is not necessary to
                  fulfill the indispensable purposes described above.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  OBLIGATIONS AS PROCESSOR OF PERSONAL DATA
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300">
                  Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez receives from third parties
                  transfers of personal data of data subjects who have pending
                  legal relationships with them, or in order to comply with the
                  various services for which third parties hire us. With
                  respect to such data, Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez acts as a
                  PROCESSOR and by Law is prevented from resolving ARCO rights.
                  In these cases, if you wish to exercise your ARCO rights,
                  you must do so before the Controller of such processing.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  RETENTION OF INFORMATION
                </h2>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
                  <li>
                    <strong>Recruitment, selection and hiring of personnel:</strong>
                    Will be destroyed no later than twelve months after the conclusion
                    of contractual obligations.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Visitor Registration:</strong> Will be destroyed
                    and/or deleted within the period that the organization
                    stipulates from the date of the data subject's visit.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">
                  ACCEPTANCE OF TERMS
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300">
                  This Privacy Notice constitutes a legally valid agreement.
                  Any change to this privacy notice will be communicated by
                  publication on its website <a
                    href="https://www.pazoschavez.mx"
                    class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300"
                    >www.pazoschavez.mx</a
                  >
                </p>
              </section>

              <div class="mt-8 pt-8 border-t border-gray-700">
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-2">
                  <strong
                    >The officer in charge of the protection of personal data
                    within Bufete Jurídico Pazos Chávez is:</strong
                  >
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-2">
                  <strong>Manuel Benítez Serrano</strong>
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                  Email: <a
                    href="mailto:privacidad@asecon2006.com.mx"
                    class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300"
                    >privacidad@asecon2006.com.mx</a
                  >
                </p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 italic">
                  Privacy Notice updated: January 8, 2024.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="mt-8 pt-8 border-t border-gray-700">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-4">
                  DOWNLOAD FORMS:
                </h3>
                <ul class="list-none space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                  <li>
                    <a
                      href="/PDF/ASECON_DERECHO_ARCO.pdf"
                      class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 inline-flex items-start"
                      target="_blank"
                      rel="noopener"
                    >
                      <span class="mr-2" aria-hidden="true">📄</span>
                      <span
                        >Request form for Access, Rectification, Cancellation
                        or Opposition of Personal Data</span
                      >
                    </a>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <a
                      href="/PDF/ASECON_REVOCACION.pdf"
                      class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 inline-flex items-start"
                      target="_blank"
                      rel="noopener"
                    >
                      <span class="mr-2" aria-hidden="true">📄</span>
                      <span>Revocation of Personal Data Form</span>
                    </a>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
